Description.LocalizedString: Once an elegant jacket and trouser combo, it has since been thrashed during one of its wearer’s frenzied states.
However torn and stained it may be, there’s still a nice green hue to it.
As his veins coursed a sickly orange color, a visceral canker wove through his spine and tore from his back.
Caught in the underworld, his flesh was torn apart by lost souls. He wore a thick girdle, foul with grease, to cover up the markings.
Remnants of clothing torn apart by sharp, impaling clusters of ice.
Was the humble robe he wore the last vestige of his humanity, or was there still something remaining inside of him?

The remains of a top hat placed upon the remains of a man.
A sophisticated top hat with a festive twist.
Forever gagging on the tendrils that wound their way up his throat, Talbot was no longer sure if his decisions were his own or those of the flourishing growth that nestled into his brain.
He found no peace in the realm beyond.
Opaline clusters of the everlasting frost pierced his jaw and punctured his eye.
The dosage of serum was more than a human body could normally withstand. The gruesome mutations were a necessary biological response to facilitate his survival.

A cane chiseled of shimmering volcanic glass and fitted with an ivory collar.
Serum seeped into the wooden finish of the cane, rejuvenating its life and creating a hybrid pustula plant.
A cursed oar used to drown those unable to pay for a safe passage.
A thick layer of ice crystallized and weighted down on his cane.
A cane with considerable weight, it’s best used when lulling victims into a false sense of security.

The vestige of his former wear, mercilessly reclaimed by nature.
A once sophisticated cane now infested with putrid mushrooms and crawling with insects.
Perhaps it was sweat… perhaps his headwear was changing form. He couldn’t be sure.
He tried to take as many samples as he could, but before long, the samples were taking him.
As time passed near the Tree of Death, the difference between reality and unreality bent and warped.
A luxurious hat he likes to wear during his New Year's hunt for serum.
His brilliant mind hid under a horrifying visage.
This new form made him more dangerous than ever.
A brutal and cruel improvised weapon.
